abstract: A recent census of German animals contains certain curious and suggestive figures. As compared with a similar census taken in 1873 it shows that most varieties of German animals have decreased in numbers within the last ten years. Germany has fewer mules, asses, and sheep and more pigs and goats than she had ten years ago, while the number of horses and oxen has very slightly increased.

abstract: CHICAGO, May 4.--The leading produce markets were very irregular to-day, with more doing. There was a general dash of weakness early, which continued till near noon, being most marked in breadstuffs. Provisions were very irregular, with more activity.

abstract: ALBANY, May 4.--The tidal wave Legislature of 1883 adjourned sine die at 7 o'clock this evening. It disappears from public view leaving behind it a record fully justifying the old saying that the Democracy is unable to bear prosperity. abstract: CHICAGO MARKETS STRONGER.  CHICAGO, May 12.--The leading produce markets were generally stronger, with a fair volume of business. Grain was firm throughout, while provisions weakened early in the day, but reacted in sympathy with breadstuffs. abstract: The wedding of the Duke of Genoa with the Princess Isabella of Bavaria, just celebrated at Castle Nymphenburg, was remarkable for good taste and simplicity.
